-- Al-Azhar Scholars Elect New Grand Mufti for Egypt, MENA Says
-- B y   M a r i a m   F a m
-- 2013-02-11T16:58:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-11/al-azhar-scholars-elect-new-grand-mufti-for-egypt-mena-says.html
     Feb. 11 (Bloomberg) --A body of senior scholars at Egypt’s
Al-Azhar, the Sunni Muslim world’s preeminent religious
institution, elected Shawki Ibrahim Abdel-Karim, as the
country’s new grand mufti.  Abdel-Karim, a professor of comparative jurisprudence at
Al-Azhar University, will succeed Ali Gomaa, whose term will
finish at the end of the month, the state-run Middle East News
Agency said. Abdel-Karim’s selection will be presented to
President  Mohamed Mursi  to issue a decree appointing the new
mufti, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mariam Fam in Cairo at 
 mfam1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
